videos.headline: USC's Stewart goes coast-to-coast with the dunk
videos.description: USC's Elijah Stewart speeds downcourt and finishes with the two-handed jam.

videos.headline: USC's Usher and Rakocevic connect for the bucket
videos.description: USC's Jordan Usher makes the fantastic overhead pass to find Nick Rakocevic for the layup.

videos.headline: USC's Rakocevic cleans up at the rim
videos.description: After Elijah Stewart misses the layup, Nick Rakocevic helps out his teammate with the putback dunk.

videos.headline: UNC Asheville splashes the clutch three
videos.description: UNC Asheville's Macio Teague sinks the wing 3-pointer as the Bulldogs battle with USC in the NIT.

videos.headline: UNC Asheville's Baehre comes up clutch
videos.description: Up two points in overtime, Jonathan Baehre knocks down the corner 3-pointer to help pad the lead and energize the offense for the Bulldogs.

videos.headline: Walton calls for more basketball
videos.description: After USC's Elijah Stewart knocks down the 3-pointer, Bill Walton hopes for double overtime.

videos.headline: UNC Asheville and USC continue to go back and forth
videos.description: UNC Asheville's Jonathan Baehre gives the Bulldogs the lead with the emphatic slam.

videos.headline: Walton gets his wish of double OT
videos.description: With less than 10 seconds to go in the game, and trailing by three, USC's Jordan McLaughlin sinks the 3-pointer to force double overtime.

videos.headline: USC's Stewart converts crucial and-1
videos.description: With a chance to take the lead, UNC Asheville's Macio Teague puts up the jumper, but Teague's shot misses and USC's Elijah Stewart gets the ball and takes it downcourt to get the three-point play.

article.headline: Short-handed USC needs 2 OTs to top UNC Asheville in NIT

images.name: Walton and Pasch react to thrilling game in the NIT
images.caption: After USC's Jordan McLaughlin sinks the teardrop shot, Bill Walton and Bill Pasch cannot contain their excitement in double overtime.

article.linkText: Short-handed USC needs 2 OTs to top UNC Asheville in NIT
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Jordan McLaughlin had 26 points and 13 assists, Nick Rakocevic added 24 points with 19 rebounds and short-handed USC needed two overtimes to beat UNC Asheville 103-98 on Tuesday night in the NIT's first round. McLaughlin was fouled on a drive with 25.1 seconds left in regulation and made two free throws to tie it at 70 after the Trojans had made just five of their first 16. UNC Asheville dribbled down the clock, but Ahmad Thomas' contested jumper was short. Jonathan Baehre faked a high screen and rolled for an open dunk to give UNC Asheville an 83-82 lead in the first overtime. After a USC miss, Macio Teague made two free throws at 13.6 for a three-point lead but McLaughlin drilled a 3 to tie it at 6.4 and Teague was short at the buzzer. McLaughlin's rainbow floater over Teague gave USC a 96-95 lead and after Teague was short on a step-back jumper, Elijah Stewart had a fast-break 3-point play for a four-point lead. UNC Ashville's Raekwon Miller made a free throw with 2.8 to go and intentionally missed the second but USC secured the rebound. Stewart added 22 points for USC (24-11), which advanced as a top-seed to face Western Kentucky. Chimezie Metu, leading the team with 15.7 points and 7.4 rebounds, electing not to play to help stay healthy for the upcoming NBA Draft. Baehre scored 28 points and grabbed 13 rebounds -- both career highs -- for his third double-double of the season for UNC Asheville (21-13). Teague added 26 points with six 3-pointers.
